column5: This big guy has been hanging around all day, hope he doesn't grab one of my song birds that spend the winter here.
Lew, he is waiting for the critters that will go for the dropped seeds. I had to take mine down due to the fact it attracted nice and voles, chipmunks I did not mind.
He's definitely not there for the seed lol
Great picture Lew. We have all kinds of furry and feathery critters at our feeders at the cottage but never an Owl. Thx for sharing.

Our old pal Photoz had a knack for finding and photographing them...I have a lot of his pictures on file... Never see any hereabouts but sumpin' around here eats the mice we catch and disposeÂ  of in the woods
